story.title: Littlefield - Part 12
story.storyDescription: Sarah finds a dead body in the woods and uncovers a dark and deadly mystery.

messages.text: Helena?? Where are the buses!!??
I tried to make them hold out, but they wouldn’t. You have to believe me!
Where are my parents?? Are they still at the station!?
I saw them get on one of the other buses
Are you positive?? Why would they get on without us??
I think they told them that they were bringing you
So they LIED. AGAIN. WHY???
I think they took everyone at the station so nobody else would get wind of the buses
So nobody knows?
I mean I’m sure people saw, but didn’t understand what was happening.
Where are you??
In the car with Jared, his Mom, Sarah, some guy named Doug and Nora.
She’s not doing well.
What happened to her?
She was bit.
Oh my God...
Maybe you guys should go to the hospital and just hole up there while they take care of this.
She could be the perfect excuse to get a room and stay in there.
We passed the hospital. They locked the doors.
They WHAT
H, it’s Jared. Where the fuck are you??
We’ve been driving down 95 North for quite awhile now
And you don’t know where the final destination is??
No. But I’m trying to find out so you guys can follow us.
They made us sit quiet when we first got on the bus so they could tell us what was happening
And what did they say this place was?
It’s some village the government set up in case anything like this happened.
It’s kind of like a fortress they said.
What are they planning on doing with the problem?
They told us not to worry about that and just focus on living our lives until it’s taken care of
Okay, well, if they’re done with the BS orientation. Find out where the address is.
Okay. I’m just going to go up and ask the bus driver.
We’re heading onto 95N now.
I didn’t even have to ask!
What!? It’s Corinne again
He had his GPS on with the destination up top.
It’s 45 Andrew Circle...Claddack, New Hampshire
So across state lines...okay...I told Jared. How far away is that
The GPS said 2 hours
Oh my God...
What
It’s Nora...she’s garbling something in this deep voice.
What is she saying???
She keeps saying This is the End over and over
Oh my God...Sarah just tried to reassure her she’s going to live...
and she just said This Is the End of Everything and passed out.
I don’t think she’s breathing.
WHAT
We just pulled over. That guy Doug is trying to do CPR on her on the street
Tell him to get off of her!
WHY!?
Because she’s going to turn and what if others come!!
Maybe she won’t!
She will. That’s what they’re saying happens.  GET HIM OFF OF HER
Oh my God you’re right Oh my God...
What’s going on?? Did she bite him??
Corinne??
Corinne???
He shot her
What!? Who? Doug??
Jared
SHE’S STILL MOVING!
You have to shoot her in the head. That’s what they say to do
Did he do it???
Yes
Are you okay??
No...what do we do now?
You have to get on the road
We can’t just leave her here to rot.
Well you can’t bury her either
She saved my life.
What does Jared’s Mom say?
She’s not saying anything. She’s been catatonic since I got in the car
What does Jared say?
He wants to leave her
Just leave. We can say some sort of prayer for her later
We all can’t just pick up and leave as easily as you
I had no choice! I tried to get out and save you and they locked me in a room!
They forced me on this bus!
I know, I’m sorry.
What did you guys decide
We’re going to get back on the road.
We’ll all be together soon.
We’re on our way...
an hour later
H, it’s Jared again
How far away are you?? We just pulled in
We’re stuck at state lines.
There are armed guards everywhere and won’t let us cross over
WHAT
Yeah...they said we’re not fucking allowed to go...
and when we asked about St. Rhiannon they denied it existed
So what are you guys going to do!?
Can you talk to one of the officials and see what they can do.
Tell them we’re bringing Sarah and Corinne to her parents and they have to let us through
Okay.
They won’t do it either!! Is there another way around???
Jared??
JARED???
I have a plan...
What is it???
